Just so that people are made aware, and to remove all ambiguity - the fee of
$3.42 is the cost of the paypal transaction.

Paypal charges for cross border purchases which are clearly laid out in the
Fees portion of the paypal site. For transactions from outside US/Canada to
North American accounts  for amount of minimal value there is a 3.9% charge
+ .30 USD added to the transaction (This is paypal and not BGR).

These type of fees you agree to when using Paypal for such transactions
(including refunds and transfers from merchant accounts).

In this case .039 * 80.00 + .30 = $3.42

I am posting this to make people realize that this is a fee tacked on for
Paypal and not BGR.

Mike
